Sudan (AP) _ President Omar el-Bashir launched a diplomatic offensive to protest the U.S. missile strike on a factory in the Sudanese capital.
The United States said the plant produced the ingredients of chemical weapons.
American missiles also struck suspected bases of Muslim extremist Osama bin Laden in Afghanistan.
U.S. officials said the factory in Sudan made chemical weapons agents; Sudan maintains it's a pharmaceutical plant.
Egypt (AP) _ Libyan leader Moammar Gadhafi _ still on crutches from a recent hip operation _ led hundreds of chanting Libyans in a rally condemning U.S. missile strikes on Sudan and Afghanistan.
